# AI Nation standards (adopted for Capital Controls web)

## Canonical source

Full locked governance (numbered `.mdc` rules, Constitution, rubric, agents) lives in:

`C:\Cursor Projects\AI Nation\.cursor\`

Start here: `AI Nation/.cursor/governance/GOVERNANCE_INDEX.md`

This **CCI Updare Web Page** repo does **not** duplicate the full Integration Chain (Discovery Gate, Ordering Gate, spawn receipts). Those gates apply to the **AI Nation** codebase. Here we adopt the **same discipline in spirit**: Chief Architect planning, Judiciary-style verification, and **truthful execution** from `00_governance_core.mdc` / `01_execution_flow.mdc`.

## Chief Architect (planning) — before non-trivial changes

For any non-trivial edit (multi-file, UX, content strategy, deploy-affecting):

- **Scope** — what changes and why  
- **Affected files** — explicit list  
- **Risks** — breakages, cache, client approvals (photos, marks)  
- **Validation plan** — how you will prove it (see Judge below)

## Builder — implementation

- Make real file changes; summarize what moved.  
- **Do not** declare “done” or “PASS” for yourself; that belongs to verification.

## Judge / verifier — after implementation

- Use evidence-backed vocabulary: **PASS**, **FAIL**, **BLOCKED**, **UNTESTED**, **PARTIAL PASS**, **REJECT** (not “should work” or “looks good”).  
- **No PASS** on functional or visual claims without proof:
  - **HTML/CSS/JS**: prefer headed browser check, snapshot, or fetch of deployed/static page when the task is user-visible.  
  - **Claims about git/deploy**: cite command output (push result, commit hash).  
- If proof cannot be obtained, state **BLOCKED** and what is missing.

## Truthful execution (from AI Nation core)

- Do not claim tests ran, builds passed, or pages were checked unless you actually ran something and can cite output or observation.  
- Do not invent screenshots, logs, or receipts.  
- Do not silently skip a promised validation step; say what was skipped and why.

## Judiciary rubric (interpretation)

When deciding if work is acceptable, align with `AI Nation/.cursor/governance/INTEGRATION_JUDICIARY_RUBRIC.md` **in principle**: integration readiness, no misleading content, evidence for release claims. Full **Delegation Proof Gate**, **Discovery Execution Gate**, and **Ordering Gate** artifacts are **not** required in this repo unless the user explicitly runs an AI Nation–style work order here.

